results.title: Never give up
results.creator_credit: Haris Fazlic, ACMI Digital Storytelling and ACMI
results.brief_description: Haris Fazlic got sick of being larger than his classmates and took up exercising and, eventually, discovered his passion for wrestling. This passion has driven him to win many times despite having to overcome a major obstacle on the way. Wrestling has taught Haris that you should never give up on something you love, no matter what.

results.title: NBA Jam Tournament Edition for Game Boy
results.creator_credit: Acclaim Entertainment Ltd and Torus Games
results.material_description: Cartridge videogame. Cartridge in plastic cartridge case
results.brief_description: An update from NBA Jam, the Tournament Edition continues to employ the fast and action-packed and unrealistic form of basketball from the original. Up to four players players can take part in the two versus two matches, with each controlling a single person for their team. The computer fills in for for missing players. The Tournament Edition increases each team’s roster to three, and allows for substitutions between quarters. Shoving players now results in injuries, which lower a player’s stats, which subbing recovers. New additions the Edition include randomized zones on the court that reward extra points for making a basket while standing within them, powerups that help with scoring or hurt the other team and Juice Mode, which increases the speed of the game.

results.title: The Journey
results.creator_credit: Christopher Tuckfield, Patricia L'Huede, Film Finance Corporation Australia and Aeriel
results.brief_description: Based on the moving portrayal of the extraordinary journey to Japan of 74 year-old Billie Sinclair, who is deaf, blind and mute. Billie has been deaf since the age of two and lost his sight at age ten, but despite this he is a dedicated traveller who funds his trips by weaving and selling baskets. The landscape of his travels is one of touch and smell, imagination and even memory, for he can still remember the time before he lost his sight as a child. This remarkable man has survived and thrived. His is not a handicap but a blessing for it has encouraged him to keep searching and learning. In Japan he rides a roller coaster, tries his hand at Judo and visits a deaf and blind acupuncturist. His world is so sensual, one almost envies it. This documentary achieves a miraculous thing; it transports those possessed of all their senses into a world where communication is by touch alone. And even more miraculously, this world does not terrify.

results.title: Enemy Infestation for PC
results.creator_credit: Ripcord Games and Micro Forte Studios
results.material_description: CD-ROM videogame. CD-ROM, CD jewel case, manual and registration in cardboard box
results.brief_description:
In the remote human colony on Redavi, an alien spaceship filled has crash-landed and creatures within have begun to mercilessly attack the colonists. Its only hope is a small squad of human defenders, their wits and whatever they can scavenge.

The game is set over 27 squad-based real time strategy missions with a large variety of tasks, ranging from rescuing fellow colonists to exterminating all the aliens. A unique feature is the overall mission structure, where the player has multiple missions to choose from. The game supports multiplayer up to 4 players on LAN and Internet and single player co-op.

A unique feature is the overall mission structure, where the player has multiple missions to choose from. The game supports multiplayer up to 4 players on LAN and Internet and single player co-op.

results.title: The Jolifou inn
results.creator_credit: Colin Low, Tom Daly and National Film Board of Canada
results.brief_description: Canada of a hundred years ago seen through the paintings of Cornelius Krieghoff, celebrated Dutch artist and adventurer. The changing seasons, the untamed beauty of the Quebec countryside and the French settlers among whom he lived were an unending source of inspiration to Krieghoff, whose work is a colourful record of French-Canadian life in the mid-19th century. Photography by Lyle Enright and Douglas Roberts. Edited by Colin Low. Music by Louis Applebaum. (Awards: Yorkton; Bilbao; Toronto; Kootenay)

results.title: The Jimi Hendrix Experience: electric ladyland
results.creator_credit: Roger Pomphrey, Bous De Jong, Nick de Grunewald, BBC, Experience Hendrix, Daniel Television and Isis Productions
results.brief_description:
Episode of Series “Classic albums: the greatest records in rock history”.
Jimi Hendrix’s album “Electric Ladyland” is one of the classic rock albums of the 20th century. With songs like “Voodoo Chile”, “Crosstown Traffic”, “Gypsy Eyes”, and “All Along the Watchtower”, it has influenced countless rock guitarists. This documentary, part of the “Classic Album” series, examines both the recording process of the album as well as focusing on the life and legend of Jimi Hendrix. Examining each song on the album, the documentary intersperses interviews with Hendrix’s friends and musicians who played on the album, with footage of Hendrix both playing and being interviewed, photos (including Linda McCartney’s pictures for the album cover), and Hendrix’s notes and journals as well as lots of amazing music. People interviewed include Chas Chandler, Mitch Mitchell, Noel Redding, Buddy Miles, Dave Mason, Mike Finnigan, Steve Winwood and album engineer Eddie Krammer.
